---
import MainLayout from '../../../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import GuideDetail from '../../../../components/resources/GuideDetail.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../../../components/resources/Breadcrumbs.astro';

const title = 'Investment Guide | Severino Realty';
const description = 'Institutional-grade playbook for sourcing, underwriting, financing, operating, and exiting residential investments.';

const steps = [
  {
    id: 'thesis',
    heading: 'Investment Thesis & Box',
    pdfUrl: '/docs/resources/thesis-box.pdf',
    bodyHtml: `
      <p>Define a narrow buy box so decisions are fast and repeatable. Your box should be objective and testable.</p>
      <h4>Market & submarket</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Jobs and population: 3–5 yr CAGR trending positive; employer diversity; landlord-friendly regulatory climate.</li>
        <li>Submarket hygiene: crime trend ↓, school ratings, healthcare access, transit, flood/fire risk scores, insurability.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Asset & strategy</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Asset type: SFR, small MF (2–20), or condo—avoid mixed HOA risk unless reserves and bylaws are strong.</li>
        <li>Strategy: Core (stabilized), Value-add (light CapEx with rent lift), or Opportunistic (heavy rehab). Pick one.</li>
        <li>Unit mix & size: min 2 bed where families dominate; target efficient layouts; avoid functionally obsolete plans.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Return guardrails</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Entry yield: in-place cap ≥ local debt cost + 150–200 bps or path-to-coverage within 12–18 months.</li>
        <li>DSCR targets: ≥ 1.25× at <em>actual</em> rates and taxes; stress at +200 bps and 10% lower NOI.</li>
        <li>IRR/MoIC gates: 5-yr project IRR ≥ 14–18% depending on risk; equity multiple ≥ 1.8–2.2×.</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'source',
    heading: 'Deal Sourcing & Screening',
    pdfUrl: '/docs/resources/deal-sourcing-checklist.pdf',
    bodyHtml: `
      <p>Run a consistent funnel with fast kill rules. Protect underwriter time.</p>
      <h4>Channels</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Broker network: weekly WIP calls; send buy box; provide rapid feedback to stay top-of-mind.</li>
        <li>Direct-to-owner: mailers, SMS (opt-in compliant), door knocks on micro-farms, probate/eviction lists.</li>
        <li>Digital: MLS alerts, auction platforms, wholesaler lists vetted for assignability and clean title.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Fast screen (5–10 min)</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Location pass/fail, year built, bed/bath, parking, HOA constraints, rent control, deed restrictions.</li>
        <li>Back-of-envelope: stabilized rent, Opex %, taxes at reset, insurance quote, maintenance/CapEx reserve.</li>
        <li>If DSCR &lt; 1.1× on in-place and &lt; 1.2× on pro forma → kill. If title/permit red flags → hold for clarification.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Pipeline hygiene</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Single source of truth (CRM/Sheet). Stages: New → Screening → LOI → Underwriting → PSA → Diligence → Close.</li>
        <li>For each stage: owner, next action, deadline, probability, and blocker. Cull dead leads weekly.</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'model',
    heading: 'Underwriting & Diligence',
    pdfUrl: '/docs/resources/underwriting-diligence-checklist.pdf',
    bodyHtml: `
      <p>Underwrite conservatively and verify every input. The model is only as good as source documents.</p>
      <h4>Core inputs</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Rent roll and T12; normalize with vacancy (5–8%), credit loss, concessions, and seasonality.</li>
        <li>Taxes: reset to purchase price; confirm millage and exemptions; model annual reassessment where applicable.</li>
        <li>Insurance: bindable quotes with wind/flood endorsements; loss runs; roof age and 4-point reports.</li>
        <li>Utilities & contracts: water/sewer allocation, trash, pest, landscape, laundry, PM fees.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>CapEx & scope</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Mechanical/structural first: roof, HVAC, plumbing, electrical, envelope, moisture remediation.</li>
        <li>Unit turns: finish level by strategy; budget contingency 10–15%; include permit fees and carry.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Sensitivity & risks</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Run data tables on rent growth (±2%), exit cap (±100 bps), rate (+200 bps), and timeline slippage (+3–6 months).</li>
        <li>Exit tests: break-even occupancy and DSCR; equity at risk if cap rates decompress.</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="text-sm"><strong>Compliance:</strong> fair housing adherence, lead/asbestos awareness, local rental licensing, and short-term rental ordinances.</p>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'finance',
    heading: 'Finance Structure',
    pdfUrl: '/docs/resources/finance-structure-guide.pdf',
    bodyHtml: `
      <p>Match debt to business plan. Liquidity kills deals—secure buffers.</p>
      <h4>Debt options</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Bank/credit union: relationship pricing, recourse; best for light value-add with clear DSCR.</li>
        <li>Agency/small balance: non-recourse, prepay penalties; sizing on DSCR and LTV.</li>
        <li>Bridge: CapEx heavy, interest-only; require rate caps and strict draw management.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Key terms & protections</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>LTV/LTC: cap leverage so post-stabilization DSCR ≥ 1.30×. Require <strong>interest rate cap</strong> on floaters.</li>
        <li>Reserves: taxes/insurance impounds; replacement reserves; operating reserve ≥ 6 months of debt service.</li>
        <li>Covenants: distribution blocks under DSCR triggers; reporting cadence; cure rights and carve-outs.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Equity stack</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>LP/GP split with preferred return and catch-up; clear promote hurdles; full fee schedule disclosed.</li>
        <li>Subscription docs, AML/KYC, Form D where required; investor portal and quarterly reporting templates.</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'operate',
    heading: 'Asset Management',
    pdfUrl: '/docs/resources/asset-management-playbook.pdf',
    bodyHtml: `
      <p>Execution drives returns. Manage to metrics, not anecdotes.</p>
      <h4>Operating system</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>KPI dashboard: occupancy, pre-lease %, delinquency, turnover time, effective rent, maintenance SLA.</li>
        <li>Cadence: weekly PM call; monthly variance report vs. budget; quarterly portfolio review with action items.</li>
        <li>Vendor management: service level agreements, insurance certs, scope templates, and competitive bidding.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Rent & renewals</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Revenue management: market comps weekly; renewal offers 75–90 days out; track acceptance and churn.</li>
        <li>Collections: firm policy ladder; payment plans documented; eviction workflow compliant and humane.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Value-add execution</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Turn schedule with critical path; batch materials; QC checklist; before/after photo documentation.</li>
        <li>Amenity ROI tests: laundry, parking, storage, pet fees; implement only with measured payback &lt; 24 months.</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
  {
    id: 'exit',
    heading: 'Hold/Exit & Tax',
    pdfUrl: '/docs/resources/exit-tax-guide.pdf',
    bodyHtml: `
      <p>Plan the exit on day one. Returns concentrate at disposition.</p>
      <h4>Hold tests</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Annual hold/sell/refi analysis with broker BOV. Trigger if unlevered IRR forward &lt; hurdle or capital at risk ↑.</li>
        <li>Refi screens: DSCR ≥ 1.25× post-refi; avoid cash-out that breaches tax or loan covenants.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Disposition</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>12–18 month prep: cure deferred maintenance, stabilize collections, package diligence room (leases, estoppels, permits, CapEx logs).</li>
        <li>Broker process: targeted list, clear TIs, buyer reps, clean PSA, and tight milestones.</li>
      </ul>
      <h4>Tax & proceeds</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Model depreciation recapture and capital gains; evaluate 1031 exchange, DST, or opportunity zone timing.</li>
        <li>Distribute per waterfall; deliver investor tax packs (K-1s) with audit trail.</li>
      </ul>
    `,
  },
];

const checklistUrl = '/docs/resources/investment-due-diligence-checklist.pdf';

const related = [
  { title: 'Buying Guide',       href: '/resources/guides/buying',           desc: 'From search to ownership.',         image: '/images/guides/buying.webp',      alt: 'New homeowners with keys' },
  { title: 'Selling Guide',      href: '/resources/guides/selling',          desc: 'Prep, pricing, marketing, closing.', image: '/images/guides/selling.webp',     alt: 'Staged living room ready for sale' },
  { title: 'Renting & Landlord', href: '/resources/guides/renting-landlord', desc: 'Screening, leases, compliance.',     image: '/images/guides/renting.webp',      alt: 'Keys and lease documents' },
];
---

<MainLayout {title} {description}>
  <GuideDetail
    title="Investment Guide"
    intro="From sourcing to exit with disciplined underwriting and operating control."
    estReadMin={18}
    {steps}
    {checklistUrl}
    {related}
  >
    <Fragment slot="breadcrumbs">
      <Breadcrumbs
        items={[
          { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
          { label: 'Resources', href: '/resources' },
          { label: 'Guides', href: '/resources/guides' },
          { label: 'Investment' }
        ]}
      />
    </Fragment>
  </GuideDetail>
</MainLayout>
